comments.content: Could be custom. Alternates: [FF Prater](http://web.archive.org/web/20081201122759/http:/www.fontshop.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=catalog.fontpackage&startrow=1&records=&currpage=1&totalrecords=20&displayfontid=FF.11198.0.0&fontRendererText=POSTPUNKITCHEN), [Cafeteria](http://web.archive.org/web/20081201122759/http:/www.fontshop.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=catalog.fontdetail&displayfontid=FB.6917.0.4&attributes.sampleSize=48&sampleText=POSTPUNKITCHEN&sampleSize=48), [Sarcastic Girl Scout Bitch](http://web.archive.org/web/20081201122759/http:/www.core.nu/freefonts.html), [Comrade](http://web.archive.org/web/20081201122759/http:/www.fontshop.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=catalog.fontpackage&startrow=1&records=&currpage=1&totalrecords=3&displayfontid=FB.104963.0.0&fontRendererText=POSTPUNKITCHEN)

I agree that this is probably custom. The ’P’s, ’N’s, and ’K’s do not match each other.

- Lex

Thanks. I would say Comrade is certainly the closest in terms of feel. To me the logotype/Comrade have sort of a picassoesque/cubist character. Can you think of any other along those lines? I may start a thread in the Design forum about this.
